{
  "texts": [
    "We show that sufcient capital accumulation is essential to prevent automation from depressing wages.",
    "Adding xed factors like land causes wages to eventually decline.",
    "Yet automating innovation itself can restart wage growth after an initial automationdriven collapse.",
    "The novel compute-centric approach opens up a new perspective for analyzing the economic impact of articial intelligence.",
    "Interesting next steps include incorporating labor and capital adjustment costs, modeling endogenous innovation, analyzing distributional impacts more fully, studying macroeconomic dynamics and policies, and evaluating the possibility of an intelligence explosion with AGI."
  ]
}